Class Venue

java.lang.Object
Venue
public abstract class Venue extends Object
The `Venue` class holds the data for a venue where events are held.
Since:
November 19, 2023

  • Constructor Details

    • Venue

      public Venue(String venueName, int pctSeatsUnavailable, String venueType, int capacity, int cost, double vipPct, double goldPct, double silverPct, double bronzePct, double generalAdmissionPct, double reservedExtraPct, boolean fireworksPlanned, int fireworksCost)
      Constructs a `Venue` object with the specified characteristics.
      Parameters:
      venueName - The name of the venue.
      pctSeatsUnavailable - The percentage of seats that are unavailable.
      venueType - The type or category of the venue.
      capacity - The maximum seating capacity of the venue.
      cost - The cost associated with the venue.
      vipPct - The percentage of VIP seats.
      goldPct - The percentage of Gold seats.
      silverPct - The percentage of Silver seats.
      bronzePct - The percentage of Bronze seats.
      generalAdmissionPct - The percentage of General Admission seats.
      reservedExtraPct - The percentage of extra reserved seats.
      fireworksPlanned - A flag indicating if fireworks are planned.
      fireworksCost - The cost of fireworks if planned.
